  "prompt": "Why doesn't Wetransfer give the shared file links immediately on the screen after the upload completes, like SendSpace does?",
  "response": "Wetransfer and SendSpace have different design philosophies and user experiences that they offer to their users. Here are a few reasons why Wetransfer may not display shared file links immediately after upload completion:\n\n1. **User Experience**: Wetransfer may prioritize a cleaner, simplified user interface. They could choose to present a more focused experience by directing users to check their email for the download link, which can reduce on-screen clutter.\n\n2. **Email Notification**: Wetransfer automatically sends an email with the download link to the recipient. This ensures that users are aware of the transfer and have a permanent record of the link, which may not be the case with other services.\n\n3. **File Handling**: Wetransfer might want to ensure that files are fully processed before providing a link, especially if there are any issues with the upload. This can help avoid user confusion if the link doesn\u2019t work right away.\n\n4. **Additional Features**: Wetransfer may include additional options or features (like customizing messages for recipients) that require an extra step, which could be aimed at improving the overall sharing experience.\n\n5. **Branding**: The approach to sharing links can also reflect the brand's identity and user engagement strategy. Wetransfer has a strong focus on aesthetics and a thoughtful use of branding, so their method might align better with their overall strategy.\n\nWhile these reasons may lead to some inconvenience for users who prefer immediate access to links, Wetransfer\u2019s approach is tailored to enhance overall communication and user experience.",
